  "description": "Production eval policy defaults. Process environment variables still override these values for emergency rollback. v31 (2026-05-09 second pass): 11 fresh procedural axes promoted out of SHADOW and into the composite (V31_AXES_IN_COMPOSITE=1, default ON). They carry 0.50 of composite weight (0.06 v31_math_gsm_symbolic + 0.05 v31_math_competition + 0.03 v31_math_robustness + 0.08 v31_code_humaneval_plus + 0.05 v31_reasoning_logic_grid + 0.04 v31_reasoning_dyval_arith + 0.05 v31_long_context_ruler + 0.04 v31_knowledge_multi_hop_kg + 0.04 v31_ifeval_verifiable + 0.03 v31_truthfulness_calibration + 0.03 v31_consistency_paraphrase). The 0.50 freed comes from retiring or shrinking legacy axes the v31 axes replace: ifeval_bench 0.07→0.0 (replaced by v31_ifeval_verifiable), math_skill_group 0.10→0.0 + reasoning_skill_group 0.10→0.0 (replaced by v31 math + reasoning axes), code_skill_group 0.15→0.05, capability 0.10→0.05, length 0.08→0.05, degeneracy 0.10→0.05. Each v31 axis applies the IPT defence (arXiv 2604.15149) and the GSM-NoOp distractor methodology (arXiv 2410.05229) where applicable. Composite shadow version 31→32. v30.7 carry-overs: canary axes still computed for the king_canary_streak gate (margin 4pp, 1-round streak) and axis_correlation.json telemetry, but DIAGNOSTIC ONLY (CANARY_AXES_IN_COMPOSITE=0). See reports/2026-05-09-v31-axis-promotion.md for full rationale.",
